notes: Tissue type: Tissue, Smooth muscle, Artery, Aorta, thoracic; Age: 6; Age Unit: MO; Remarks: Large white domestic breed. The age of the donor is estimated. The thoracic aorta was removed immediately post-mortem on 10/15/85. Strips of the medial layer were removed, minced, and used as explants to initiate the culture. Cell morphology is fibroblast-like. The karyotype is 38,XX; normal diploid female. The culture tested positive for alpha-smooth muscle actin and negative for the endothelial cell-specific von Willebrand factor (immunofluorescence assays). For lifespan determination this cell line was cultured on gelatin-coated flasks and the medium was supplemented with crude ECGF (0.11mg/ml) and heparin (0.1mg/ml). An endothelial cell culture from this pig is AG08472A.

notes: Tissue type: Tissue, Smooth muscle, Artery, Aorta, thoracic; Age: 8; Age Unit: WK; Remarks: Yorkshire breed. The thoracic aorta was removed immediately post-mortem on 7/23/91. Strips of the medial layer were removed, minced, and used as explants to initiate the culture. Cell morphology is fibroblast-like. The culture is a mosaic with karyotype: 37,XX-1/38,XX; 6%/94%. The culture tested positive for alpha-smooth muscle actin and negative for the endothelial cell-specific von Willebrand factor (immunofluorescence assays). Culture medium: HF12 15U. The HF12 medium used should be endotoxin-free. For lifespan determination this cell line was cultured on gelatin-coated flasks. Cells were frozen in growth medium containing 7.5% polyvinylpyrrolidinone and 5% DMSO.

notes: Tissue type: Tissue, Endothelial, Artery, Aorta, thoracic; Age: 3; Age Unit: MO; Remarks: Yorkshire breed. The thoracic aorta was removed immediately post-mortem on 2/27/92. The culture was initiated using cells released from the lumen of the vessel by collagenase digestion. The cell morphology is polygonal. The culture tested positive for the endothelial cell-specific von Willebrand factor and negative for alpha-smooth muscle actin (immunofluorescence assays). The culture was grown in medium which was supplemented with  ECGS (0.02 mg/ml) and heparin (0.05 mg/ml). Culture medium: HF12 with 10% plasma-derived donor horse serum with supplements. The HF12 medium used should be endotoxin-free. The karyotype is 38,XX with 2% of the cells examined showing random chromosome loss.
